 <dc:title>Cloning of orthogonal mixed states entails irreversibility</dc:title>
 <dc:creator>Horodecki, Michal</dc:creator>
 <dc:creator>De, Aditi Sen</dc:creator>
 <dc:creator>Sen, Ujjwal</dc:creator>
 <dc:subject>Quantum Physics</dc:subject>
 <dc:description>  Orthogonal pure states can be cloned as well as deleted. However if there is
an initial disorder in the system, that is for orthogonal mixed states, one
cannot perform deletion. And cloning, in such cases, necessarily produces an
irreversibility, in the form of leakage of information into the environment.
</dc:description>
